OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F352A1688309604
OL,7,F"A handful of relatively minor
OL,8,Fconcessions were offered 48 hours
OL,9,Fbefore our first stike date in March.
OL,10,FWe walked out, taking all but two TV
OL,11,Fregions off air that evening, and a
OL,12,Fsignificant part of radio output. We
OL,13,Fhoped they would listen.
OL,15,F"Further concessions were tabled in
OL,16,FMay in talks brokered by ACAS. The
OL,17,Fonly democratic thing to do was put
OL,18,Fthat to our members. Three additional
OL,19,Fweekend breakfast shows weren't
OL,20,Fenough, and the proposals were
OL,21,Frejected.
OL,3,CLocal BBC TV, radio and online
OL,4,Cservices in England hit by strike
